%N A183654 Number of (n+1) X 2 0..5 arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 10.
%H A183654 Zhuorui He, <a href="/A183654/b183654.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a> (first 200 terms from R. H. Hardin)
%H A183654 Christian Krause, <a href="/A183654/a183654.txt">Proof of formulas</a>, Jun 12 2026.
%H A183654 <a href="/index/Rec#order_06">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (21,-175,735,-1624,1764,-720).
%F A183654 a(n) = 21*a(n-1) - 175*a(n-2) + 735*a(n-3) - 1624*a(n-4) + 1764*a(n-5) - 720*a(n-6).
%F A183654 G.f.: 2*x*(73 - 1200*x + 7409*x^2 - 21234*x^3 + 27792*x^4 - 12960*x^5) / ((1 - x)*(1 - 2*x)*(1 - 3*x)*(1 - 4*x)*(1 - 5*x)*(1 - 6*x)). - _Colin Barker_, Apr 02 2018
%F A183654 a(n) = 6*6^n + 10*5^n + 8*4^n + 6*3^n + 4*2^n + 2. - _Christian Krause_, Jun 12 2026
%e A183654 Some solutions for 3 X 2:
%e A183654 ..1..5....3..5....2..5....2..5....3..2....0..5....0..4....4..1....1..4....4..4
%e A183654 ..0..4....2..0....1..2....1..2....5..0....4..1....4..2....5..0....5..0....2..0
%e A183654 ..4..2....3..5....4..3....5..2....4..1....2..3....2..2....3..2....0..5....3..5
%t A183654 A183654[n_] := 6*6^n + 10*5^n + 8*4^n + 6*3^n + 4*2^n + 2;
